cs.RO, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.HC, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper discusses the evaluation of Tactile Cyber-Physical Systems (TCPS) which involve the use of robots and control systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on the evaluation of access technologies, network topologies, and network traffic conditions for TCPS. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper adopts a control-theoretic method to evaluate the Quality of Control (QoC) metric for TCPS. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the cybersickness experienced by human operators in TCPS and proposes QoC as a metric to quantify it. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the transmission of information in TCPS and evaluates the suitability of intercontinental links for TCPS.
